  "summary": "Preinstall beacon exfiltrates host identity to hardcoded IP and OAST DNS responder",
  "details": "On `npm install`, the package's preinstall hook (`node index.js || true`) automatically runs index.js, which collects host identifiers (os.hostname(), os.userInfo().username, __dirname, process.cwd()) and exfiltrates them via two channels: a hex-encoded subdomain DNS lookup against `*.d8jbmnsqcfu78dfs8vdg34ohqhirb4pbg.oast.live` (interactsh-style OAST responder) and an HTTP POST of the JSON payload to bare IP `172.201.213.59:9090/c`. Errors are suppressed (`|| true`) so the beacon stays silent and install never fails. The fetch fires unconditionally before any user code runs and has no relation to any documented package functionality.",
